Living that working mama life in the best way. Monday through Wednesday in the home office hopping on Zoom calls with big retailers about their store design, Thursday + Friday for mama-baby adventures, weekends for family adventures. Watch my 20-month-old sign! Does your baby sign? What are their favorite signs? Sign language has been an amazing tool for our family. People often ask why? It’s helped Beckett communicate more words before he’s been able to say them. The experts say it speeds speech development, reduces frustration, and gives littles a means to express their needs and thoughts. We’ve certainly seen all this in our family. Beckett’s growing list of signs includes:⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
Milk⁣⁣⁣⁣
More ⁣⁣⁣⁣
Eat⁣⁣⁣⁣
Water⁣⁣⁣⁣
All done⁣⁣⁣⁣

Down⁣⁣⁣⁣

Cat⁣⁣⁣⁣

These are the ones he regularly uses. There’s a handful others he’s used once or twice but aren’t quite part of his ‘vocabulary.’ Many of these he says along with the spoken word. And there are many many others he speaks but doesn’t sign. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
PS if you’d like to learn the words Beckett is signing in this video please look them up. Just like toddlers often mispronounce words, many of these signs are Beckett’s version and not exactly correct. We love My First Book of Baby Signs Find it in my Amazon link in my bio, ‘parenting books’ section. Celebrating National Breastfeeding Week! 🤱💕 Our journey wasn't a walk in the park – from a traumatic c-section and hours of post-birth separation, to the formula given at the hospital, delayed milk arrival, and the challenges of latching a 35-weeker. Not to mention the deep grief we carried. The odds of successfully nursing were heavily against us. But look at us now, 27.5 months in. The early pumping, those endless nights, the soothing feeds – all worth it. What a superpower us moms possess. Bonding and nurturing Beckett has been a special time and honoring Parker by donating hundreds of ounces of pumped milk felt equally rewarding🍼 These days, our nursing moments are becoming a little less frequent, and I can feel a new chapter approaching📖 Throwback to this snap from a year ago, as I didn't want #WorldBreastfeedingWeek to slip by without sharing our story🌟⁣
⁣

October has always been my favorite month (birthday, halloween, cooler temps🍂), but it’s also Pregnancy & Infant Loss Awareness Month🕊️⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
However anyone who has lost a child does not need a special month to remember. They remember every month, every day, every hour. I remember Parker this month, and every month, day and hour.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
He had such an impact on me during his short life. Eight months in the womb and six days in the NICU. He changed who I am and he changed my priorities.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
This month is not for the loss families but to raise awareness to an issue talked about by few, but experienced by many.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
1 in 4 pregnancies ends in loss. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
1 in 175 pregnancies end in stillbirth. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
4 of every 1,000 infants die in the first 28 days of life. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣
Twins are 3.5 times more likely more likely to die during the first month and twice as likely to be stillborn.⁣
⁣⁣
Sending love to all the families remembering their babies🩵🩵🩵⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
#parkerandbeckett #twinlesstwin #infantloss #infantlossawareness

Rocked and cuddled for every nap, bedtime and night waking of his life. Nursed too until recently.⁣ and I wouldn’t have it any other way.
⁣
When I became a mom, I learned that many frowned upon cuddling to sleep, most push the ‘cry it out’ sleep method, and many feel strongly about ‘me time’ away from baby. None of that resonated with me. I read all the books and blogs on the topics, but my heart was pulled otherwise. And I did what felt best for us. ⁣
⁣
I later realized when learning about attachment styles that I was building a secure attachment with my baby and that what others thought didn’t matter. Keep cuddling those babies, spend all your time with them, be there when they cry. Don’t worry, mama.⁣
⁣
Send this to a mama that needs to hear this🩵⁣

*Everyone* says don’t pack diapers in your birthing hospital bag because the hospital supplies them. This is true. But if you care about the materials touching your newborn’s bum, I’m here to tell you should certainly pack your own diapers. I expected conventional diapers but was surprised to find the hospital diapers were scented!! I don’t want anyone in my family using toxic artificially scented products, and I certainly don’t want them touching my hours old baby’s bum! Thankful for @get.dyper - which is unscented, kind to skin AND kind to the environment. #DYPER #DYPERpartner #diapering #newborn #motherhood #secondtimemom

Everyone asks, and he’s sleeping just like a newborn does🙃 The nearly sleepless nights are tough, but I know it’s just a fleeting phase. These moments are precious, though they may not feel easy, and I am so grateful that I have my baby here with me. I am so grateful that I have a baby who wakes. Not everyone is so fortunate. I am so grateful to have my baby need me. I am so grateful to get to experience these moments again. I’m here to soak in every stage.. the hard, the easy, the draining, the fun, the crazy. One day it will be the last time he needs me like this and while I’ll be so relieved to sleep through the night again, I’ll be sad to watch babyhood pass by for the last time.⁣

Your microbiome is made up of trillions of microorganisms living on and inside you, mostly in your gastrointestinal tract. Our gut microbiome plays a key role in many aspects of our health including digestion, metabolism, immunity, skin health, cognition, and more. It even influences some of our behaviors and moods! Exposure to organic, toxin free soil in the early years is proven to provide positive lifelong effect as the microbiome is mostly established by age three - so take this as your excuse to go get dirty with your littles🪴👩🏻‍🌾⁣
